            <thetext>&quot;Note  As of Internet Explorer 11, the Microsoft vendor prefixed version of this event (MSPointerCancel) is no longer supported and may be removed in a future release. Instead, use the non-prefixed lowercase name, pointercancel, which is better for standards compliance and future compatibility.&quot;

Microsoft has decided to rename its pointer events without any deprecation time.

That is why qx.Mobile did not work anymore on IE11 (did not receive any touch events) because we could not recognize the new names of the pointer events.

These new events are:

MSPointerOut &gt;&gt; pointerout
MSPointerUp &gt;&gt; pointerup
MSPointerMove &gt;&gt; pointermove 

etc.

The touch core handler should to be updated.</thetext>
